data.title: Nice atmosphere
data.text: Very friendly server.quick to come to our table.soup was just ok.sandwich was tasty. Rather expensive. Probably would go back.horrible parking on this street!

data.title: So happy we visited the Cannery Market!
data.text: The Cannery Public Market is an indoor public market housed in the old Larson Canning Company. The Cannery Public Market features fresh off the farm meats, vegetables, dairy, whole grains, along with many other food items! We can't wait to go back to purchase some of  their fresh farm meat!!

data.title: Favorite spot in Green Bay!
data.text: My partner and I were looking for a spot to eat one evening and this seemed like a good spot. It is was a little more expensive than we wanted, but we got such amazing food we didn't care. We got beers first, and they had a nice draft list. I got the lamb sliders for my main meal. They were incredible. Everything about them was perfect. We also had excellent service. Can't wait to go back!

data.title: Nice place
data.text:
We shared the artichoke dip appetizer which is served with pit wedges - very good. My dinner was a pasta dish with chicken, bacon and asparagus - this also was very good. Large portion allowed me to enjoy it again for lunch the next day.
There didn't appear to be much for seating. Was told that they also serve on the rooftop but with it being cold, that wasn't an option for us. I would imagine the wait for a table could be quite long at times.
The service was awkward. From the bartender who told us how important tips are to her but yet dumped out my glass of wine before I was done with it, to the server who brought our appetizers without any plates to eat it on, to the difficulty in getting someone to get us water to the waitress who forgot to bring back our credit cards.

Nice to have a restaurant in the Green Bay area that has good food at reasonable prices.

data.title: Expensive
data.text: The food was outstanding but expensive . The service was good. The wait staff did a good job very informative .

data.title: Great food
data.text: Nice open restaurant and market.  The Wisconsin grilled cheese sandwich (deep  fried cheese curds and bacon) was fabulous!  Server very friendly.  Great place to eat lunch.

data.title: Dinner
data.text: The Cannery was recommended by a local. This is an organic farm fresh restaurant that also has a deli and sells fine etc...We ordered the salmon and the pork chop, both were awesome. Definitely check this place out. It's also right next to the Title town Brewery.

data.title: Great atmosphere, good food
data.text: Went here with my wife when we were visiting Green Bay and we loved the place. Fried cheese curds were great and I got a pulled pork and granny smith apple crepe that was really fun and different. Neat atmosphere with the market area and a good drink selection as well. The building is unique and the service was excellent.

data.title: Beautiful!
data.text: We went there for Bloody Mary's on Sunday before the game and were glad we did. The bar was great and the market has a wide variety or cheeses and meats! I would recommend it to anyone!

data.title: Food was good but expensive.
data.text: $6.50 for tappers and wine for $10.00 is a bit much for this place. The food was good and everything on the menu looked good. We had salad and a beef patty and flatbread and fries. All good and fresh. Service was excellent. The atmosphere is lacking. At these prices I expect linen table clothes.

data.title: Great!
data.text: I ate here because it was walking distance from the Hampton. Great choice! The bourbon chicken was awesome! As was the rosemary roasted red potatoes. The chicken was served on the best tasting greens I've ever eaten. The pumpkin cheesecake was fantastic too!

data.title: Good atmosphere
data.text: We went here for appetizers and drinks. The food was good, maybe a little expensive, but I could tell it was made with fresh ingredients. The drinks were the only downside-- too pricey. $9 for a mojito? I don't know... seemed a little much to me. I would recommend that they invest in more comfortable chairs for the rooftop bar too.

data.title: Nice lunch
data.text: My husband and I stopped here for lunch.  We both got the burgers, halfway through I realized I hadn't used any ketchup, I didn't need to it was so good.  I have also had one of the flatbreads here.  It was good too.  Nice atmosphere,  almost forget you are in Green Bay.

data.title: Long Wait Time and a Cold Crepe
data.text: Went here on a Sunday morning to try the brunch.  There were quite a few empty tables so we didn't fore see any problems getting our meal in a timely fashion.  I ordered the Wild Berry Blintz and my boyfriend ordered the Meat Lovers Skillet.  We waited almost 30 min before the manager came over and told us that the kitchen was running a bit behind and that our food would be out shortly.  It came out about ten minuets later.  My boyfriend's skillet was good, but my wild berry crepe was cold and the crepe tasted like it was just a raw sheet of pastry dough.  I did ask the waitress if it was supposed to cold and she said yes.  Not sure about this as all of the crepes that I have ever eaten have been warm.  Needless to say that while I did not send it back, I did not eat it.  The manager did take note of this and made it right by not charging us for it.  I would give this place a second chance as maybe the kitchen was just having an off day but they would really have to blow me away to remove a that bad first impression.

data.title: best place for a meal in green bay
data.text: had some really good vegetarian options including the flat breads, the mac n cheese was sumptious! The coffee was good as well.

data.title: Great, holesome, locally sourced meals in fitting atmostphere
data.text: Classic merging of good food, locally sources ingredients, fun atmosphere paying homage to the farming communities of north east Wisconsin. Well worth the stop. Shop with wide variety of Wisconsin products there as well.

data.title: Resturant and Grocery all in one.
data.text:
I guess I would say this is an experience. It is like nothing I have seen before.

 All of the food is purchased locally when in season and of high quality.  They have the menu set up so you know where the items are from ( supplier ) 

My husband inquired about a dish and thank goodness for the waitress who explained that he may want to make another selection. She indicated that the item was being removed from the menu in the near future and explained the dish. Thank goodness so on her recommendation he made an alternative choice. I really give the waitress credit for knowing that the selection most likely wasn't going to meet his needs. 

I also liked the grocery section, with choices of beer, wine, meat, jams, seasoning. If you like to cook you will really enjoy this section. 

I am guessing the wine selection must be really good as I noticed 80% of the groups at least one person was drinking wine. 

We will go back wish I would have found this gem sooner.

data.title: We ate a great dinner and bought provisions for dinner at home the next night
data.text: We are staying with friends who warned us of "the noise" but said it was a great experience and it was. We had a bit of a wait but we went upstairs to hear a oompa German band and see the skyline. Fun! We shopped the market while we waited and based on the flat iron steak samples being circulated, we bought a steak and seasoning to make at home on Saturday. They even told us how to prepare it.  They were accommodating on husband and I request to split a salad and split an entree and everything was very good.  The house salad split was more than enough!!

data.title: Very Good!
data.text: If you're looking for locally sourced food not your typical junk, this is the ticket! Got the porketta, delish!

data.title: Good service but blah food
data.text: Our waitress was great, but the food was very disappointing. Most of what we had was just okay - edible but not enjoyable. Our party had all 3 soups and one was too spicy (with no forewarning of spiciness), one was too sweet (who ever heard of sweet French Onion soup??), and the third was just "meh". The mac & cheese was so bland that I had to take it home and add salt, and my friend didn't even bother to take hers home. A sandwich was also very bland and overpriced for what it was, and the cheese curds were overcooked and a little greasy. The only thing that anyone in our party rated as good was the porchetta. The ambiance inside is nice/trendy, but we sat by the window/garage door, the entire outside of which is covered with spiders, which is kind of gross to look at while dining.
